How to prepare a new release:

1. Check in all changes.
2. Update the ChangeLog. Use 'svn log -r HEAD:lastHead' in order to create
	the list of changes.
3. Also change Makefile.version.
4. Check these changes in using the message "New version (psmgmt-x.y.z)".
5. Tag the new release using 'make -C dist tag'.
